wiki.content: “BULERÍAS” is the fourth track of ROSALÍA's third album, "MOTOMAMI" -- an introspective song where Tobella highlights hardship she had endured in her life. She thanks a few of her idols (such as M.I.A. and Tego Calderón), as well as her loved ones for inspiring her to begin a music career. The song also flaunts her extensive knowledge of flamenco (which she is college-educated in). As the track progresses, it grows increasingly more dense and gradually switches to Bulerías -- a traditional derivative of flamenco music which both originate from Andalusia. Here, she begins interpolating the song "Bulerías de la Perla" by Camarón de la Isla; while reaffirming herself as a force to be reckoned with, in an almost explosive, 'crescending' ritual of sorts.
